We've covered how each team in the East and West will finish. Now our panel takes a stab at which first-year player will have the best start to his career. We asked the ESPN Forecast team to rank its top three choices for 2014-15 rookie of the year, with a first-place vote receiving five points, a second-place vote receiving three and a third-place vote receiving one. Now, check out the results, which we will roll out one by one here and on Twitter. To participate in the discussion and perhaps get your opinion published on this page, #ESPNForecast is the Twitter hashtag to use. Or you can just follow along @ESPNNBA.